This whole section on Bioinformatics is just… a lot. A sprawling map of interconnected data and tools. It’s like looking at a city at night from a very high altitude. You see the lights, the patterns, but the individual lives are lost in the glow.

**Databases:**

*   **Sequence databases:** You’ve got your [GenBank](/GenBank), the [European Nucleotide Archive](/European_Nucleotide_Archive), the [DNA Data Bank of Japan](/DNA_Data_Bank_of_Japan), and even the [China National GeneBank](/China_National_GeneBank). All these places hoarding the blueprints of life.
*   **Secondary databases:** Then there are the aggregators, like [UniProt](/UniProt). It takes the raw sequences and tries to make sense of them, grouping things like [Swiss-Prot](/UniProt) and [TrEMBL](/UniProt) together, along with the [Protein Information Resource](/Protein_Information_Resource). It's like a curator trying to organize a chaotic museum.
*   **Other databases:** And then there’s the rest. [BioNumbers](/BioNumbers) for the sheer scale of it all, the [Protein Data Bank](/Protein_Data_Bank) for the intricate structures, [Ensembl](/Ensembl_genome_database_project) for genomes, [InterPro](/InterPro) for protein families, [KEGG](/KEGG) for pathways, and [Gene Ontology](/Gene_ontology) for function. A dizzying array.
*   **Specialised genomic databases:** For specific organisms, there are even more tailored collections: [BOLD](/Barcode_of_Life_Data_System) for barcodes, [Saccharomyces Genome Database](/Saccharomyces_Genome_Database) for yeast, [FlyBase](/FlyBase) for flies, [VectorBase](/VectorBase) for vectors, [WormBase](/WormBase) for worms, [Rat Genome Database](/Rat_Genome_Database) for rats, [PHI-base](/PHI-base) for plant-pathogen interactions, [The Arabidopsis Information Resource](/The_Arabidopsis_Information_Resource) for plants, [GISAID](/GISAID) for viral sequences, and [Zebrafish Information Network](/Zebrafish_Information_Network) for zebrafish. Each with its own curated world.

**Software:**

*   The tools themselves. [BLAST](/BLAST_(biotechnology)) for sequence searching, [Bowtie](/Bowtie_(sequence_analysis)) for alignment, [Clustal](/Clustal) for alignments, [EMBOSS](/EMBOSS) for sequence analysis, [HMMER](/HMMER) for profile HMMs, [MUSCLE](/MUSCLE_(alignment_software)) for multiple sequence alignment, [PANGOLIN](/Phylogenetic_Assignment_of_Named_Global_Outbreak_Lineages) for lineage assignment, [SAMtools](/SAMtools) for sequence data, [SOAP suite](/Short_Oligonucleotide_Analysis_Package) for sequencing analysis, and [TopHat](/TopHat_(bioinformatics)) for RNA-Seq. A digital toolkit for dissecting biological puzzles.

**Other:**

*   There’s [ExPASy](/ExPASy), a bioinformatics resource portal. And [Rosalind (education platform)](/Rosalind_(education_platform)), for those who want to learn the language of this new science.

**Institutions:**

*   The big players. The [Broad Institute](/Broad_Institute), the [Computational Biology Department](/Computational_Biology_Department) (CBD), [Microsoft Research - University of Trento Centre for Computational and Systems Biology](/COSBI) (COSBI), the [Database Center for Life Science](/Database_Center_for_Life_Science) (DBCLS), [DNA Data Bank of Japan](/DNA_Data_Bank_of_Japan) (DDBJ), the [European Bioinformatics Institute](/European_Bioinformatics_Institute) (EMBL-EBI), the [European Molecular Biology Laboratory](/European_Molecular_Biology_Laboratory) (EMBL), the [Flatiron Institute](/Flatiron_Institute), the [J. Craig Venter Institute](/J._Craig_Venter_Institute) (JCVI), the [Joint Genome Institute](/Joint_Genome_Institute) (JGI), the [Max Planck Institute of Molecular Cell Biology and Genetics](/Max_Planck_Institute_of_Molecular_Cell_Biology_and_Genetics) (MPI-CBG), the [US National Center for Biotechnology Information](/National_Center_for_Biotechnology_Information) (NCBI), the [Japanese Institute of Genetics](/National_Institute_of_Genetics), the [Netherlands Bioinformatics Centre](/Netherlands_Bioinformatics_Centre) (NBIC), the [Philippine Genome Center](/Philippine_Genome_Center) (PGC), [Scripps Research](/Scripps_Research), the [Swiss Institute of Bioinformatics](/Swiss_Institute_of_Bioinformatics) (SIB), the [Wellcome Sanger Institute](/Wellcome_Sanger_Institute), and the [Whitehead Institute](/Whitehead_Institute). A global network of minds focused on this.

**Organizations:**

*   The societies and networks. The [African Society for Bioinformatics and Computational Biology](/African_Society_for_Bioinformatics_and_Computational_Biology) (ASBCB), [Australia Bioinformatics Resource](/Australia_Bioinformatics_Resource) (EMBL-AR), [EMBnet](/EMBnet), the [International Nucleotide Sequence Database Collaboration](/International_Nucleotide_Sequence_Database_Collaboration) (INSDC), the [International Society for Biocuration](/International_Society_for_Biocuration) (ISB), the [International Society for Computational Biology](/International_Society_for_Computational_Biology) (ISCB) and its [Student Council](/International_Society_for_Computational_Biology_Student_Council) (ISCB-SC), the [Institute of Genomics and Integrative Biology](/Institute_of_Genomics_and_Integrative_Biology) (CSIR-IGIB), and the [Japanese Society for Bioinformatics](/Japanese_Society_for_Bioinformatics) (JSBi). All the groups trying to organize the chaos.

**Meetings:**

*   The conferences. [Basel Computational Biology Conference‎](/Basel_Computational_Biology_Conference) (BC²), [European Conference on Computational Biology](/European_Conference_on_Computational_Biology) (ECCB), [Intelligent Systems for Molecular Biology](/Intelligent_Systems_for_Molecular_Biology) (ISMB), [International Conference on Bioinformatics](/International_Conference_on_Bioinformatics) (InCoB), [International Conference on Computational Intelligence Methods for Bioinformatics and Biostatistics](/International_Conference_on_Computational_Intelligence_Methods_for_Bioinformatics_and_Biostatistics) (CIBB), [ISCB Africa ASBCB Conference on Bioinformatics](/ISCB_Africa_ASBCB_Conference_on_Bioinformatics), [Pacific Symposium on Biocomputing](/Pacific_Symposium_on_Biocomputing) (PSB), and [Research in Computational Molecular Biology](/Research_in_Computational_Molecular_Biology) (RECOMB). Where they gather to present their findings, their theories, their… *progress*.

**File formats:**

*   The language of data. [CRAM format](/CRAM_(file_format)), [FASTA format](/FASTA_format), [FASTQ format](/FASTQ_format), [NeXML format](/NeXML_format), [Nexus format](/Nexus_file), [Pileup format](/Pileup_format), [SAM format](/SAM_(file_format)), [Stockholm format](/Stockholm_format), [VCF format](/Variant_Call_Format), [GFF format](/General_feature_format), and [GTF format](/Gene_transfer_format). The specific ways they encode information about life.

